The 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference is the premier event of its kind in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and cloud community. This year, the conference will be hosted on 6 June 2019 at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand, Gauteng. Most of South Africa’s premier cloud, hosting, data centre and cloud telecoms providers have already confirmed their participation in the conference. These companies include Liquid Telecom, Connection Telecom, VMWare, Teraco, Axis, Microsoft, Mimecast, Fortinet, Cipherwave and Miro. Other conference sponsors include Westcon, Redstor, Elingo, Egoli Gas, Galix, Continuity SA, and Quick Connect. Delegates will also hear from the country’s top experts in the field, including Liquid Telecom CEO Reshaad Sha, VMWare’s Dave Funnell, and Google Cloud specialist Brett StClair. Registrations for the 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference are open and MyBroadband readers can register at a big discount using the voucher code below. Please note that a limited number of tickets will be available using this discount code.